<h2 id="section-top">Respiratory Medicine</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1431">Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">Chest Clinic<br/>020 3192 6888</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent6c3739288b6e41e5ba332d2c22f2aece">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Chest Clinic" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=1859"/>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Lewisham Healthcare NHS Trust offers a wide range of services to treat all respiratory disorders, and provide a number of specialist clinics including:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Cystic Fibrosis </li>
<li>Tuberculosis (TB)</li>
<li>Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD)</li>
<li>Severe COPD</li>
<li>Asthma</li>
<li>Unexplained Cough </li>
</ul>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>What Respiratory Services are available?</strong></p>
<p>The Trust provides specialist clinics for the following conditions:</p>
<ul>
<li>Lung cancer </li>
<li>Tuberculosis (TB) and TB in HIV </li>
<li>Asthma </li>
<li>Chronic obstructive airways disease </li>
<li>Pleural diseases </li>
<li>Cough </li>
<li>Joint service with the Rheumatology Consultant for patients with autoimmune disorders </li>
<li>Assessment for pulmonary rehabilitation </li>
<li>Cystic fibrosis and transition </li>
</ul>
<p>The Trust also provides a range of diagnostic services and link with other specialties such as oncology and radiotherapy, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Oxygen assessment </li>
<li>Over night sleep assessments </li>
<li>Lung function tests </li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Where are the Respiratory Services based?</strong></p>
<p>Respiratory services are provided from the dedicated Chest Clinic (Suite 5) at University Hospital Lewisham. You can find Suite 5 on the 1st floor of the Yellow Zone.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Further information</strong></p>
<p>For further information, including clinic times, referral details and key staff, please <strong><a href="http://www.lewisham.nhs.uk/our_services/specialist_medicine/respiratory_services.aspx">visit the respiratory medicine section of our website</a></strong>.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
